1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the effects of blockage on an end-to-end application over a mmWave cellular link, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the effects of channel dynamics on the quality of the mmWave cellular link, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of mmWave for wireless communications, which is related to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.AR (Augmented Reality) - The paper discusses the effects of blockage on the channel quality, which is relevant to augmented reality applications that rely on stable and high-quality wireless connections. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper discusses the use of a phased array system to measure the channel in multiple directions, which is related to multi-agent systems that coordinate the actions of multiple agents to achieve a common goal.
